text:
160-162 Riverside Drive, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of 88th Street.

1923.

Gift of E. M. Jenks.

folder: 88th Street and Riverside Drive, Manhattan, N.Y.
text:
A garden and path to a squatters cabin at about West 88th Street and the Hudson River.

April 29, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Squatters Colony at the Hudson River.

folder: 88th Street and Riverside Drive, Manhattan, N.Y.
text:
(1)
Squatters shack, stilted over the Hudson River's edge, at about West 89th Street.
April 29, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, a closer view, showing two curious visitors.
April 29, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.

(3)
Squatters lunching amid the ruins of their shacks (wrecked by a sudden storm), at the Hudson River's edge, at about West 88th Street.
April 29, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
title: Squatters Colony at the Hudson River.
